# Using - https://github.com/Huachao/vscode-restclient

### liveness endpoint
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/health

### Readiness endpoint
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/health/ready

### Test healthcheck
# GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/healthcheck
# GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/unknown
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/sample-api/healthcheck

### test db
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/sample-api/check-db

### HTTP Testing

GET https://randomuser.me/api/
Accept: application/json 

### Test Post

POST https://httpbin.org/post
Accept: application/json

### Test Login - Username & Password
POST http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/auth/login
content-type: application/json

{
  "email": "test",
  "password": "test"
}

### Test Login - OTP
POST http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/auth/otp
access_token:
refresh_token: 
content-type: application/json

{
  "id": 1,
  "pin": "111111"
}

### Post Test - will cause an error because content-type and body is different
POST http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/sample-api/tests/test-post-json
content-type: application/json

hello world

### Post Test SSE endpoint
POST http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/sample-api/sse/event
content-type: application/json

{
  "bye": "everybody"
}

### Spawn python process (detached) — expects {} back
# Requires python3 at PYTHON_BIN path (default: /usr/bin/python3)
# On Windows set PYTHON_BIN=C:\Python312\python.exe in .env.local
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/sample-api/tests/python

### Download a file — normal case
# Place a file in the upload folder first, then request it by name only
# Expected: file streams back as application/pdf
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/sample-api/tests/download?filename=test.pdf

### Download — path traversal attempt (should NOT serve /etc/passwd)
# path.basename strips ../../ so this looks for 'passwd' inside the upload folder
# Expected: file-not-found error, NOT the contents of /etc/passwd
GET http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/sample-api/tests/download?filename=../../etc/passwd

### use data from file
# POST http://127.0.0.1:3000/api/test-xml
# content-type: application/xml
#
# < ./demo.xml

### Multipart Form Sample
# POST https://api.example.com/user/upload
# Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW

# ------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
# Content-Disposition: form-data; name="text"

# title
# ------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4YWxkTrZu0gW
# Content-Disposition: form-data; name="image"; filename="1.png"
# Content-Type: image/png

# < ./1.png
# ------WebKitFormBoundary7MA4Y
